    "The obtained g update satisfies",
    ", which ensures that the gradient descent optimization along g update always minimizes both losses simultaneously.",
    "Crucially, this solves the gradient-level conflict between the objectives: rather than allowing one loss to dominate or oppose the other, this formulation ensures that both objectives contribute constructively to each optimization step adaptively.",
    "This prevents the optimizer from getting trapped in regions where one loss is minimized at the expense of the other, a common failure mode in standard weighted objectives.",
